# 🎯 Test Strategy Guidelines

> High-level strategy governing all test planning decisions in this project.
> Aligned with the evaluation criteria: business-critical focus, quality over quantity.

---

## ⛔ Human Approval Gate

**CRITICAL: The AI agent MUST NOT write or modify code without explicit verbal approval.**

- Every proposed change must be **described in natural language first**
- The engineer reviews, approves, adjusts, or rejects before any code is written
- This prevents AI-slop and ensures every line of code is intentional

---

## 🧭 Core Principles

| Principle | Description |
|-----------|-------------|
| **Business-first** | Focus on flows that impact revenue and user experience — booking, payments, availability |
| **Happy + Negative** | Every feature covers success paths AND failure/edge scenarios |
| **Explicit validation** | Validate error messages explicitly — don't assume generic checks are enough |
| **No redundancy** | Avoid overlapping test coverage — each test must add unique value |
| **Maintainability > Quantity** | Fewer well-structured tests beat many fragile ones |

## 📊 Methodology — Equivalence Class Partitioning + BVA

### Equivalence Class Partitioning (ECP)
- Group inputs into **equivalence classes**: valid, invalid-empty, invalid-below-min, invalid-above-max
- Select **one representative value** per class — reduces redundant tests
- Goal: minimize test count while maximizing defect detection

### Boundary Value Analysis (BVA)
- Within each equivalence class, test at **exact boundaries**: minimum, maximum, below-min, above-max
- Comment character lengths next to every fixture field for traceability
- Each boundary is a separate test case

### Combined Strategy
- ECP defines **which classes** to test → BVA defines **which values** within each class
- Result: minimum number of tests with maximum validation coverage

## 🐛 Bug Discovery Strategy

- Use `test.fail()` to document known application bugs
- Write tests asserting **ideal behavior** — when bugs are fixed, tests auto-pass
- Never skip bugs — `test.fail()` keeps the pipeline green while documenting the defect

## 📱 Multi-Viewport Coverage

- Test critical flows on **desktop, tablet, and mobile** viewports
- Use `test.fail()` with viewport conditions for responsive bugs (e.g. `BUG-014`)
- Visual regression tests target **desktop only** (stable baseline environment)

## 🏗️ Architecture Alignment

- **API tests**: `request` fixture, Zod schemas, factory fixtures
- **UI tests**: Page Object Model, `readyLocator` pattern, no selectors in specs
- **Shared**: Types in `tests/types/`, fixtures in `tests/fixtures/`, config in `tests/config/`
